First, install Kubernetes and Helm if you haven't already.
Add the Airbyte Helm repository:

    helm repo add airbyte https://airbytehq.github.io/helm-charts
    helm repo update


helm install airbyte airbyte/airbyte -n airbyte -f values.yaml
    helm install airbyte airbyte/airbyte -n airbyte -f ./helm/values.yaml

forward port
    kubectl --namespace airbyte port-forward service/airbyte-airbyte-webapp-svc 8000:80
    "Visit http://localhost:8000"


check chart version and deployments
    helm list -n airbyte -f airbyte


Redeploy a deleted deployment
    helm upgrade --install airbyte airbyte/airbyte --set worker.enabled=true --reuse-values -n airbyte


check the logs of a pod
    kubectl logs -f airbyte-worker-767db5b6c7-4smkp -c airbyte-worker-container -n airbyte


After updaing the values.yaml file use this to reapply changes

    helm upgrade <RELEASE_NAME> <CHART_NAME> -f path/to/new/values.yaml -n <NAMESPACE>
    helm upgrade airbyte airbyte/airbyte -f ./helm/values.yaml -n airbyte


uopdate version
    helm upgrade <RELEASE_NAME> <CHART_NAME> --version <CHART_VERSION> -f ./helm/values.yaml -n airbyte
    helm upgrade airbyte airbyte/airbyte --version 0.43.29  -f ./helm/values.yaml -n airbyte



search for a helm repo
    helm search repo airbyte


helm repo remove
    helm repo remove [REPO1 [REPO2 ...]] [flags]

Add the Bitnami repository to Helm with the following command:
    helm repo add bitnami https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami


